name: Mein Herz weiß genau, was es will
comments: In Germany, Ralph Maria Siegel wrote two German texts. The first title "Mein Herz weiß genau, was es will" was intended for Connie Francis . Although it was produced in Hollywood on October 18, 1960, it was not initially released. It only appeared in 1988 on a Bear Family compilation. After he initially found no buyers for his text, he wrote a second version with the title "So wie es damals war". Three producers were immediately found for this text, and in October 1960 they released recordings with Gina Dobra (Polydor), Nana Gualdi (Philips) and Siw Malmkvist . The Austrian record company Austroton followed suit with Trixie Kühn None of the German cover versions reached the charts.

name: Times Gettin' Hard, Boys
comments: Folk song collected by Carl Sandburg in South Carolina and included in his 1927 book, "The American Songbag." Sandburg learned it from an elderly woman who learned it as a child. Versions of this song have been traced back to the mid 1800s. Lee Hayes, who was familiar with Sandburg's book,  copyrighted this song in the 1950s based on new lyrics. However, the first recording of this song attributed to Lee Hayes was by Pete Seeger in 1955 and it was very close to Sandburg's version.
